  "texts": [
    "Data bias in models likeChatGPT refers to the presence of unfair or systematic preferences in the training data, originating from various sources including data collection, societal biases, and inherent biases in the data sources.",
    "Language models like ChatGPT are trained on vast amounts of internet text data, which can introduce biases related to gender, race, religion, and other aspects of identity, leading the model to reproduce such biases in its responses.",
    "Data bias can result in discriminatory responses, assumptions, or inaccuracies based on the biased patterns learned during training.",
    "Addressing data bias is an active research area, aiming to identify and mitigate biases during training to enhance fairness and inclusivity in these models, but it remains a complex challenge requiring continuous efforts and collaboration for meaningful progress.",
    "Open ProblemsLanguage models like ChatGPT, including Large Language Models (LLMs), have limitations despite their impressive performance."
  ],
